main event: Multiple white, solid objects were observed flying in the sky over Cotati, California on August 16, 1952.
interesting points: The objects appeared one at a time and traveled at speeds of 50-150 mph, flying against the wind at an altitude of about 300 feet.
The observer, a Ground Observer Corps member, removed her glasses but could still see the objects clearly.
Several other people in the area also reported seeing the same objects.
The last object hovered for about 5 minutes before making a quick dash to the north and then disappearing to the southwest.
The observer thought the objects might be 'Skyhook' balloons from Tillamook, Oregon, but this was inconclusive.
sighted object: 8 white, flat, round objects approximately 25-35 feet in diameter
